Barcelona have released a strong squad to face Atlético Madrid in Thursday’s Spanish Super Cup semi-final fixture at the King Abdullah Sports City Stadium in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia. Barcelona manager, Ernesto Valverde has named a 24-man squad in a post on the club’s official website on Tuesday night. The La Liga champions head to the game following a 2-2 draw against Espanyol in their last encounter. Barcelona squad against Atletico Madrid: N. Semedo, Piqué, I. Rakitic, Sergio, Todibo, Suárez, Messi, Neto, Lenglet, M. Wague, Griezmann, Jordi Alba, S. Roberto, F. De Jong, Vidal, Umtiti, Junior, Iñaki Peña, C. Pérez, Riqui Puig, Collado, Ansu Fati, R. Araujo and Arnau Tenas. Missing due to injury are Ter Stegen, Arthur and O. Dembélé. The kick-off time for the match is 8pm.